#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:1
msgid "Document settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:4
msgid ""
"Configure resident document centralization in nursing homes (MR/MRS) — "
"root folder, default tags, automatic filing in the Documents app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:8
msgid "Where are the document centralization settings?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:9
msgid ""
"In **Settings > Documents > File centralization**, the **Nursing home** "
"block. This block only appears when the Documents app is installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:11
msgid "What exactly does resident document centralization do?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:12
msgid ""
"When enabled, every attachment added to a resident's record (chatter) is "
"automatically filed in that resident's personal folder, in the Documents "
"app. This way you find all of a resident's files in one place, with no "
"manual filing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:14
msgid "Do I have to create the \"Residents\" root folder myself?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:15
msgid ""
"No. Resthome automatically creates the \"Residents\" root folder (with a "
"\"Blank forms\" subfolder) as soon as the company is created. The \"Root "
"folder\" field already points to it; there is nothing for you to prepare."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:17
msgid "What are the default tags for?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:18
msgid ""
"It is optional. The chosen tags are automatically applied to centralized "
"documents, which then makes searching and filtering easier in the "
"Documents app. You can leave this field empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:20
msgid "Can I disable centralization?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:21
msgid ""
"Yes, by unchecking the \"Nursing home\" block. Documents already filed "
"stay in the resident folders; only future attachments are no longer "
"centralized automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:23
msgid "Is the setting shared across all my facilities?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:24
msgid ""
"No. It is specific to each company (facility) in the database. Each "
"company has its own \"Residents\" root folder and its own configuration, "
"which keeps the folders isolated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:27
msgid ""
"The **Settings > Documents** tab gathers the settings of Odoo's "
"**Documents** app. In the **File centralization** section, Resthome adds "
"a **Nursing home** block that **automatically files** your residents' "
"attachments into their **personal folder**. You find these settings in "
"**Settings > Documents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:31
msgid "File centralization**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "Prerequisite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:36
msgid ""
"These settings only appear if the **Documents** application is installed."
" The residents' root folder is created automatically — there is nothing "
"to prepare before enabling centralization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:41
msgid "Resident document centralization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:43
msgid ""
"The **Nursing home** block controls automatic document filing. A checkbox"
" enables centralization; once ticked, it reveals the **root folder** and "
"the **default tags**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "Setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "What it does"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "Recommended value (MR/MRS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "**Nursing home** (centralization)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid ""
"Enables automatic filing: every attachment added to a resident's record "
"is filed in their personal folder in the Documents app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "**Enabled** (ticked)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "**Root folder**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "The Documents app folder under which Resthome files all resident folders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "The **\"Residents\"** folder (created automatically)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "**Default tags**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid ""
"The tags automatically applied to centralized documents, to find and "
"filter them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:33
msgid "**Optional** — leave empty, or choose 1 or 2 tags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:53
msgid "The root folder is created for you"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:56
msgid ""
"When the company is created, Resthome automatically creates the "
"**\"Residents\"** folder (with a **\"Blank forms\"** subfolder for your "
"templates). The **Root folder** field already points to it. There is "
"normally no reason to change it; only modify it if you deliberately store"
" residents elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:62
msgid "One folder per resident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:64
msgid ""
"You do not create the folders by hand. When a resident is admitted (or "
"when their resident record is activated), Resthome creates their "
"**personal folder** under the root folder, with three ready-to-use "
"subfolders:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:68
msgid "**Medical documents**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:69
msgid "**Administrative documents**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:70
msgid "**Billing documents**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:72
msgid ""
"The folder is named after the **resident's name** and is renamed "
"automatically if the name changes. The **Documents** button on the "
"resident's record opens this folder directly (the counter includes the "
"files in the subfolders)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:76
msgid "Isolated per facility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:79
msgid ""
"In a multi-company setup, **each company has its own \"Residents\" root "
"folder**. The setting is **specific to each facility**: enable "
"centralization in each of them if you run several homes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:84
msgid "Default tags (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:86
msgid ""
"**Tags** are used to categorize and find documents. Resthome already "
"provides a list of ready-to-use tags — for example **Katz**, **End of "
"stay**, **eAgreement**, **OA**, **Convention**, **Medical form**, "
"**Billing**, **CPAS**, **GDPR**. In **Default tags**, you choose the ones"
" that will be applied **automatically** to each centralized document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:92
msgid "Start light"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:95
msgid ""
"Leave this field **empty** at first, or put a single generic tag in it. "
"You can always tag each document more precisely afterwards in the "
"Documents app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:99
msgid "Disabling centralization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-documents.md:101
msgid ""
"Unchecking the **Nursing home** block **stops** the automatic filing of "
"future attachments. Documents already filed in the resident folders "
"**stay in place** — nothing is deleted or moved."
msgstr ""

